Rating: 4
First of all, this is very, very good. However, the recipe states to simmer until liquid is reduced to 1 1/3 cups, about 15 minutes. Maybe the recipe takes simmer to mean a full rolling-boil but I simmered my liquid for nearly an hour until it was reduced completely and it would have been the perfect consistency had we eaten hot (like pudding). But the next day, when it was cool, the liquid was as thick as bread dough (but still yummy). So I would suggest to really only simmer for 15 minutes (maybe 30) and not worry about the actual measurement of the liquid. Also, the creme fraiche really brings all the flavors together, don't be tempted to substitute whipped cream.

Rating: 0
I make a very much easier version of this.. All I do is cut the ripe bananas put them in a bowl with a bit of lemon juice to prevent browning..I also add a bit of cuban rum to bring out the flavour of the bananas... then I just puree the bananas with the sugar syrup, the cream and vanilla, and churn it in an icecream maker.. come out perfect

